    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-06-08T09:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-06-08T09:10:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <head>208. Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d208fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Middle East Crisis. Top Secret; [<hi rend="italic">codeword not
                            declassified</hi>].</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-06-08T10:10:00-04:00">June 8, 1967, 10:10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>It looks as though <persName corresp="#p_KAN1">Kosygin</persName> may have
                    contemplated on June 6 sending additional aircraft to Egypt—but he is obviously
                    reluctant and trying to use a cease-fire to avoid that move.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d208fn2">Rostow’s memorandum forwarded [<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified</hi>] report that [<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified</hi>] was working on sending aircraft as [<hi rend="italic"
                            >text not declassified</hi>] had requested. [<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified</hi>] the Soviet Union would support the Security Council
                        proposal for a cease-fire. [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]
                        the Soviets were keeping a close watch on the movements of the U.S. and
                        British forces and [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>] U.S. and
                        British aircraft had not taken part in the hostilities.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Walt</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
